Disciple of the Five Winds</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uevokamusmaximus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evokamus Maximus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/16/01 5:09:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm..</span><hr size=1> Well I have a few beefs with the game, and I do play it.  In the cities, I get about 10FPS, which IMHO is BS, I got a pretty bad ass systme and it shouldn't run that slow.  Second, they got a memory leak the size of a grand canyon, if you whompa from OA to Newland to Tir, you better camp and reboot because your disk will thrash so much because its caching all of the info to the disk.  I've seen it some time crashing if I can get to it fast enough see the game Soaking up 400MB of Ram, now I understand that its pretty advanced game but Sheesh.  As soon as they fix those problems I'll be happy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulumpyhammerfell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lumpy Hammerfell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/16/01 5:16:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm..</span><hr size=1> The 10 FPS you are getting in the cities is attributed to the memory leak they are working on now.  The game fills up your ram but doesnt flush it and leaves it like 200 kb to swap out textures.  Thats why the game chugs like it does in the cities with the high polygon count.  Everywhere else seems to be fine for me, as i rarely crash.   IMHO its gonna be a great game when all the bugs get ironed out.  Being a newbie is great again.  =)<br>
